# Node.js & Express

## Runtime

- Node.js 22+; async/await only (no callback-style routes)
- Graceful shutdown: `SIGINT`/`SIGTERM` → close HTTP server → `prisma.$disconnect()`
- Verify DB on startup (`SELECT 1`)

## Express app (`app.ts`)

Middleware order (preserve):

1. `trust proxy`, `helmet`, `cors`, `compression`
2. `express.json({ limit: "1mb" })`, `urlencoded`, `cookieParser`
3. `pino-http`, `generalLimiter`
4. Routes `/docs`, `/api/v1`
5. `notFoundHandler`, `errorHandler`

## Async handlers

Wrap all route handlers with `asyncHandler` from `shared/utils/async-handler`.

Never leave floating promises in middleware or controllers.

## Do not

- Add Fastify, Koa, or alternate frameworks
- Use `console.log` — use Pino logger
- Block the event loop with sync crypto on hot paths beyond existing Argon2 usage
